FeedPackage.Description:
Generates static class with current Mercurial revision metadata which can be referenced in assembly attributes. It uses the same auto-versioning algorithm for build and revision number as AssemblyVersion attribute with asterisk.
Example Usage: [assembly: AssemblyVersion("1.0." + (MercurialInfo.HasChanges ? "*" : MercurialInfo.GlobalVersion))] [assembly: AssemblyInformationalVersion("1.0 (" + MercurialInfo.ChangesetID + (MercurialInfo.HasChanges ? "+" : "") + ")")]
FeedPackage.Summary: Mercurial Revision Information Code Generation Tool
FeedPackage.Tags: mercurial hg version versioning auto automatic automatically
FeedPackage.Title: HgMetal

FeedPackage.Description:
Generates static class with current Mercurial revision metadata which can be referenced in assembly attributes. It uses the same auto-versioning algorithm for build and revision number as AssemblyVersion attribute with asterisk and also considers referenced projects' revisions metadata while version calculation (dependent project update leads to master project "update" even without changes in the last).
Example Usage: [assembly: AssemblyVersion("1.0" + MercurialInfo.VersionSuffix)] [assembly: AssemblyInformationalVersion("1.0" + MercurialInfo.ChangesetSuffix)]
FeedPackage.ReleaseNotes: Some bug fixes and commonly used templates.
FeedPackage.Summary: Mercurial Revision Information Code Generation Tool
FeedPackage.Tags: mercurial hg version versioning auto automatic automatically assembly assemblyinfo assemblyversion assemblyversionattribute
FeedPackage.Title: HgMetal

FeedPackage.Description:
MSBuild task that generates a .cs file with Mercurial current revision metadata of the project at build time.
You can use it for auto-versioning, ex. [AssemblyFileVersion("2.1" + HgMetalInfo.AssemblyVersionFileTemplate)].
FeedPackage.ReleaseNotes: Rethinking of concepts and algorithms - brand-new and backward-incompatible HgMetal 2.
FeedPackage.Summary: MSBuild task that generates a .cs file with Mercurial current revision metadata of the project at build time.
FeedPackage.Tags: mercurial hg version versioning auto automatic automatically assembly assemblyinfo assemblyversion assemblyversionattribute semver semantic
FeedPackage.Title: HgMetal

FeedPackage.Description: HIDSharp is a cross-platform .NET wrapper for Windows, MacOS, and Linux (hidraw) USB HID APIs.

FeedPackage.Tags: USB HID Windows Mac Linux
FeedPackage.Title: HidSharp

FeedPackage.Description: HIDSharp is a cross-platform .NET wrapper for Windows, MacOS, and Linux (hidraw) USB HID APIs.
FeedPackage.ReleaseNotes:
1.4.0 (April 20, 2013): Documented the most important classes. Fixed a problem with output reports on 64-bit Windows. Fixed a timeout bug on Windows. Parallelized device enumeration. Reordered platform detection to prevent binary planting on Windows.
1.3 (February 23, 2013): Fixed Linux libudev reference to not require developer package symlinks.
1.2 (October 16, 2012): Fixed MacOS support.
1.1 (July 28, 2012): Added experimental MacOS and Linux support. Added experimental report descriptor parsing.
1.0 (August 28, 2010): Initial release.
FeedPackage.Tags: USB HID Windows MacOS Linux Mono
FeedPackage.Title: HidSharp

FeedPackage.Description: HIDSharp is a cross-platform .NET wrapper for Windows, MacOS, and Linux (hidraw) USB HID APIs.
FeedPackage.ReleaseNotes:
1.5 (May 18, 2013): Added the DevicePath property to HidDevice. This is useful for differentiating devices with the same VID, PID, etc.
1.4.0.1 (April 21, 2013): Added missing XML documentation file to the archive.
1.4 (April 20, 2013): Documented the most important classes. Fixed a problem with output reports on 64-bit Windows. Fixed a timeout bug on Windows. Parallelized device enumeration. Reordered platform detection to prevent binary planting on Windows.
